04/03/2011
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- EU-brokered talks between Serbia and Kosovo are expected to start on March 8th, with delegations meeting in Brussels. The session will be facilitated by EU officials, Interior Minister Bajram Rexhepi confirmed on Thursday (March 3rd), adding that US representatives will participate as well. The first meeting was arranged after continuous efforts by EU facilitator Robert Cooper. (RTK, TV 21, Kohavision, Telegrafi - 03/03/11)
